it presence and “not touched” confirmation; - files changed; - validation results; - legacy path audit; - telemetry prohibition confirmation; - known risks; - final git status.  Validation commands: From D:\rehealthAI\Android-apk run: - .\gradlew.bat testDebugUnitTest - .\gradlew.bat assembleDebug - git diff --check - git status --short --branch  Use JAVA_HOME if needed: D:\Android_Studio\jbr  Self-review searches: Run searches and summarize results: - MockPhmService - RemotePhmService - ReHealthBackendClient - ReHealthMobileApi - uploadRingSnapshot - ring/snapshots - patient/risk-score - patient/intervention-plan - features/evaluate - measurements/batch - ring_signal_chunks - PPG - RRI  Self-review requirements: Confirm: - MockPhmService is fallback only. - RemotePhmService or equivalent is primary. - HealthFeatureExtractor participates in evaluation. - /features/evaluate is canonical risk path. - /ring/snapshots is not primary risk source. - /measurements/batch is not used in P0b. - stash was not applied. - no BLE-owned files were modified. - no backend/model-service/rehealth-android files were modified.  Commit: feat(android): wire canonical risk UI path  Push: Push branch for review if remote is configured: work/P0b_android_canonical_risk_ui_path  Do not force push.  Definition of done: - Started from origin/work/D_android_network_feature_evaluate or a clean branch based on it. - Did not apply telemetry sync stash. - Did not use /measurements/batch. - Did not touch BLE/background service files. - Android model/risk UI uses RemotePhmService or equivalent primary path. - HealthFeatureExtractor participates in evaluation. - /features/evaluate is canonical. - UI displays risk score/level/contributions/model version/mock flag or preserves them in state. - Mock fallback remains available and visibly marked. - Legacy /ring/snapshots is not primary risk display path. - Tests added/updated where practical. - testDebugUnitTest passes. - assembleDebug passes. - git diff --